;B[dr]LB[dr:1]CR[cq][dq]C[Dia.2 6 points in husu

If Black plays 1 then he can capture the two stones.  The thing to be careful of in this case is the bottom White stone is not a stone White cares about.

So, you get two points from the captured stones and two points so that makes four points of territory.

2+4 = 6 points of territory.
This means that A is worth 6 points in husu.\lang1042\f1\fs18


